act = {"start": "2023-11-03 19:00", "end": "2023-11-03 21:21", "stage": "Hyde Park Picture House, Screen 1", "act": "LIFF 2023 Opening Film: Poor Things", "type": "film", "url": "https://www.leedsfilm.com/whats-on/liff-2023-opening-film-poor-things/", "blurb": "\"Everything in it \u2013 every frame, every image, every joke, every performance \u2013 gets a gasp of excitement.\" - Peter Bradshaw, Guardian\n\"Flamboyant, florid, fantastic, and freakish, this might well be one of the most unique movies you\u2019ll ever see.\" - Steph Green, Inverse\n\"Greek director Yorgos Lanthimos works on a grand scale for the first time in this spectacularly entertaining, visually phenomenal, \u201cCandide\u201d-like feminist fable.\" - Kyle Smith, Wall Street Journal\nVisionary director Yorgos Lanthimos (The Favourite, Dogtooth) invites audiences on an absurdist global odyssey celebrating female pleasure and liberation. This is the extraordinary tale of Bella Baxter (Emma Stone), a woman brought back to life by eccentric scientist Dr. Godwin Baxter (Willem Dafoe). With no knowledge of the world or societal norms, Bella's insatiable curiosity and voracious sexual appetite drives her to run away on a madcap adventure with playboy Duncan Wedderburn (Mark Ruffalo). Lanthimos masterfully crafts an outlandish and opulent world that took home the prestigious Golden Lion at Venice Film Festival.\nPlease note this screening contains scenes with flashing and flickering images which may affect viewers who are susceptible to photosensitive epilepsy.\u00a0\nThis film contains potentially triggering or sensitive content for audiences. Please click here to find out more information. Audio Description is available at both screenings at Hyde Park Picture House Screen One.\u00a0Please email leeds.film@leeds.gov.uk if you require a headset from the venue.The screening at 20:30 on\u00a04th November at Hyde Park Picture House Screen One will\u00a0be presented with additional descriptive subtitles of non-dialogue audio.\nVisit\u00a0our\u00a0Accessible Screenings at LIFF 2023 page for\u00a0more information and other accessible screenings at the festival.\nPresented in partnership with Film4\n\n\u00a0\nWatch Trailer"}
