act = {"start": "2023-11-12 13:45", "end": "2023-11-12 16:47", "stage": "Vue Screen 12", "act": "Inside the Yellow Cocoon Shell", "type": "film", "url": "https://www.leedsfilm.com//whats-on/inside-the-yellow-cocoon-shell/", "blurb": "\"The entrancing debut feature from Pham Thien An becomes a quest for understanding and certainty in a Vietnam that seems unable to provide any clear answers.\" - Allan Hunter, Screen International\n\"Challenging but seductive art cinema that invites comparisons to such titans as Apichatpong Weerasethakul, Tsai Ming-liang and even Theo Angelopoulos, without feeling derivative of any.\" - Guy Lodge, Variety\nInside the Yellow Cocoon Shell is a mesmerising spiritual road movie haunted by the beautiful landscapes of rural Vietnam. The film begins in lively, chaotic Saigon as the brooding Thien witnesses a fatal motorcycle accident. His sister in law is one of the victims and Thien is tasked with childcare duties for his 5-year-old nephew Dao. The pair gradually form an awkward alliance as they head deep into the countryside in search of the boy\u2019s father. Director Pham Thien crafts a richly cinematic, multi-layered sensory experience and a moving meditation on loss and grief.\nWatch Trailer"}
